The paper is about generating structured query language (SQL) from natural language, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves database (DB) and reinforcement learning (LG) techniques, which suggest cs.DB and cs.LG as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval (IR) tasks, which could also place it in the cs.IR sub-category.
